ABUJA – The House of Representatives on Tuesday asked the Executive arm of government to expedite necessary actions that may lead to the review or cancellation of the immigrant restriction on Nigeria by the United States of America. The House also urged its leadership to interface with every relevant government agency and diplomatic missions towards resolving the issue and preventing similar future occurrence. The decisions followed a motion of urgent national importance brought before it by Tajudeen Yusuf (PDP Kogi) on the need to unravel the circumstances that led to the immigration restriction by the United States of America, as well as seek quick resolution and prevent future occurrences. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network Yusuf, had in his motion, told the House that the United States of America on January 31, 2020, as a direct consequence of non-compliance with the established identity-management and information-sharing criteria assessed by performance metrics, placed immigration restriction on Nigeria and four other countries including Tanzania, Sudan, Eritrea, Myanmar and Kyrgyzstan. He also said that the immigration restriction on Nigeria and the countries, which was a further fallout of alleged non-adequate data sharing on public safety and terrorism-related information necessary for protection, was expected to take effect from February 21, 2020.